        <div class="col-xs-12">
            <h1 class="cd-text cd-title">tables</h1>
            <p class="cd-text">Tables should be used for tabular content such as lists of ingredients.</p>
            <p class="cd-text">You can use the <a href="http://pistachio.graze.com/basics/grid-system">bootstrap column classes</a> such as <code>col-xxs-4</code> to define percentage sizes for your table columns although these will not collapse at lower breakpoints like the grid usually does.</p>

            <div class="panel">
                <div class="panel__body">
                    <h4 class="cd-text cd-title">notes</h4>
                    <p class="cd-text">The below example uses the <code>.horizontal-overflow</code> div to contain the table with a <code>.horizontal-overflow__table</code> class applied to the table.  This ensures that overflowing tables are scrollable and not distorted for users with smaller screens. When applicable, always use this container to ensure optimal display of tables.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">basic table</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">A basic, minimal, table.</p>

            <div class="horizontal-overflow">
    <table class="table">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th class="col-xxs-4">&nbsp;</th>
                <th class="col-xxs-4">per 100g</th>
                <th class="col-xxs-4">per punnet (18g)</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>Energy</td>
                <td>2100 kJ<br>501 kcal</td>
                <td>378 kJ<br>90 kcal</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Fat<br><small>of which saturates</small></td>
                <td>24 g<br><small>7.6 g</small></td>
                <td>4.4 g<br><small>1.4 g</small></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Carbohydrate<br><small>of which sugars</small></td>
                <td>61 g<br><small>5.8 g</small></td>
                <td>11 g<br><small>1.1 g</small></td>
            </tr>
        </tbody>
        <tfoot>
            <tr>
                <td colspan="3">* no added salt – purely from naturally occurring sodium</td>
            </tr>
        </tfoot>
    </table>
</div>

